in the Olympic team event since the 2008 Games in Beijing, China.\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999940509952, \"rank\": 5.948824957754107e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 283, \"end\": 301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Figure_skating_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics_\\u2013_Team_event\", \"score\": 0.9796033952338553, \"rank\": 0.020821283979170793, \"text\": \"Olympic team event\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Figure_skating_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics_\\u2013_Team_event\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Figure_skating_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics_\\u2013_Team_event\"}, {\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.6902097175887767e-12, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999588759244642, \"rank\": 2.3847345733550683e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their 16-year-longdroughtended on July 29, 2024, with a bronze medal in the team all-around final.\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 440, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thevictorywas especially surprising after their disappointing performance in the qualifying events the previous day.\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The team came fifth in the trials, with captain Brody Malone falling during multipleroutines.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 607, \"end\": 612, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\", \"score\": 0.7931541580268674, \"rank\": 0.24365484754943453, \"text\": \"Brody\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\"}, {\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Malone\", \"score\": 0.9530265433622258, \"rank\": 0.049269638021717785, \"text\": \"Malone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Malone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Malone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malone's unusual performance wasattributedto a serious knee injury heincurred16 months ago.\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Malone\", \"score\": 0.9530265433622258, \"rank\": 0.049269638021717785, \"text\": \"Malone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Malone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Malone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It led tospeculationabout hisabilityto perform in the finals.\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the fears provedunfounded.\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 24-year-old led his five-person team with aflawlessroutine on the still rings and high bar, improving both his personalscoreand the team's overall score.\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 996, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You just got to forget about it,\\\" Malone said of his performance at the trials.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1078, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1033, \"end\": 1039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Malone\", \"score\": 0.9530265433622258, \"rank\": 0.049269638021717785, \"text\": \"Malone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Malone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karl_Malone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was over and done with.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is nothing I can do about it.\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1142, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just had to focus on the next day, and that's what we did.\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it ended up working out great.\\\"\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fellow gymnasts Paul Juda, Asher Hong, and Frederick Richard also delivered outstanding routines, boosting the team's medalprospects.\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1257, \"end\": 1266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Juda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paul Juda\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Juda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Juda\"}, {\"begin\": 1268, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asher_Hong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Asher Hong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asher_Hong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asher_Hong\"}, {\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3132418380556475e-15, \"text\": \"Frederick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_the_Great\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the final result hinged on Stephen Nedoroscik, whose only task was toexcelat thepommel horse.Nedoroscik did not disappoint.\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Nedoroscik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Nedoroscik\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hisflawlessperformance earned him a near-perfect score, securing the team's bronze medal.\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 25-year-old gymnastcementedhisreputationas the \\\"pommel horse guy\\\" with another bronze in theindividualcompetition on August 3, 2024.\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The US women's gymnastics team has been adominantforce in the sport since the Atlanta 1996 Games.\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1740, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999940509952, \"rank\": 5.948824957754107e-09, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gymnasts have won gold at every Olympic team event except the Tokyo 2020 Games.\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1870, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Figure_skating_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics_\\u2013_Team_event\", \"score\": 0.9796033952338553, \"rank\": 0.020821283979170793, \"text\": \"Olympic team event\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Figure_skating_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics_\\u2013_Team_event\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Figure_skating_at_the_2022_Winter_Olympics_\\u2013_Team_event\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Tokyo, they secured silver after Simone Biles withdrew due to a mental health condition known as \\\"the twisties.\\\"\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 2033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1921, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999419944409097, \"rank\": 5.800885232454663e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1954, \"end\": 1966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 Games was anopportunityfor the women to get back the gold medal, and they delivered.\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team captain Biles, along with Jordan Chiles, Jade Carey, and Sunisa Lee, carried outimpeccableroutines on the beam, uneven bars, and vault before dominating the floor exercises.\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2166, \"end\": 2179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 2181, \"end\": 2191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jade Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\"}, {\"begin\": 2197, \"end\": 2207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sunisa Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Theskillfulathletes decisively claimed the top spot, finishing six points ahead of silver-medalist Italy.\", \"from\": 2314, \"to\": 2419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2413, \"end\": 2418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9794207271146875, \"rank\": 0.011022375768405694, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team's success continued in the individual events.\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On August 2, 2024, Biles won gold in the all-around individual competition, while Lee took bronze.\", \"from\": 2476, \"to\": 2574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2558, \"end\": 2561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9821310687743351, \"rank\": 0.018192790912113153, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee'simpressiverun continued on August 4, 2024, with a second bronze in the uneven bars.\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2663, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9821310687743351, \"rank\": 0.018192790912113153, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old'saccomplishmentsare all the moreextraordinaryconsidering she battled two types of kidney disease over the past year.\", \"from\": 2664, \"to\": 2796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Until about six month ago, Lee was unsure she would ever compete in gymnastics again.\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2824, \"end\": 2827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9821310687743351, \"rank\": 0.018192790912113153, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jordan Chiles added to her Olympic haul with a bronze medal in the individual floor exercise competition on August 5, 2024.\", \"from\": 2884, \"to\": 3007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2884, \"end\": 2897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles clinched silver in the same event.\", \"from\": 3009, \"to\": 3049, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With anunprecedented11 Olympic medals (7 gold, 2 silver, 2 bronze), Biles is now the mostdecoratedUS Olympic gymnast in history.\", \"from\": 3050, \"to\": 3178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When asked if she would compete in the 2028 Summer Games in Los Angeles, California, Biles was noncommittal.\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3253, \"end\": 3263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 0.8043900959229685, \"rank\": 0.24317013582286276, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Never say never.\", \"from\": 3290, \"to\": 3307, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The next Olympics is at home, so you just never know,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3308, \"to\": 3372, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Resources: NPR.org, USAgym.org, theGuardian.com, CBS.com, NBC.com  I LOVE SUNI LEE <3  I live right next to the 2028 LA venue.\", \"from\": 3374, \"to\": 3500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3423, \"end\": 3430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CBS.com\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS\"}, {\"begin\": 3432, \"end\": 3439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBC.com\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope I might get to see the team.\", \"from\": 3501, \"to\": 3536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"go Simone biles  I can do a handstand, roundoff, cartwheel, and a brige  Gymnastics is too hard for me.\", \"from\": 3538, \"to\": 3641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3611, \"end\": 3621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.997071232778699, \"rank\": 0.0029373640701940377, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"gymnastics is the best.\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can do some gymnastics  I have never done gymnastics.\", \"from\": 3667, \"to\": 3722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I play field hockey and tennis, that is more my ... type.\", \"from\": 37